Arils membranous, fimbriate, covering at least half and often the entire seed; stigmas usually discrete; inner petals with differentiated fleshy margins around basal concavity; apex of anther connective conical to capitate and papillate to long-papillate, giving a bumpy rather than flat surface to the androecium (sect. 
